```spl
| Comment: Data Source Exploration Template
| Comment: Use to understand available data

| Comment: Step 1 - Sample events from the data source
index={INDEX} sourcetype={SOURCETYPE}
    earliest=-24h latest=now
| head 1000

| Comment: Step 2 - Field summary
| fieldsummary
| where count > 10
| sort - count
| table field, count, distinct_count, is_exact, min, max, mean, stdev

| Comment: --- Alternative: Event type distribution ---

| Comment: index={INDEX} earliest=-24h
| Comment: | stats count by sourcetype
| Comment: | sort - count

| Comment: --- Alternative: Time distribution ---

| Comment: index={INDEX} sourcetype={SOURCETYPE} earliest=-7d
| Comment: | bin _time span=1h
| Comment: | stats count by _time
| Comment: | timechart count

| Comment: --- Alternative: Top values for a field ---

| Comment: index={INDEX} sourcetype={SOURCETYPE} earliest=-24h
| Comment: | top limit=20 {FIELD_NAME}

| Comment: --- Alternative: Rare values (potential anomalies) ---

| Comment: index={INDEX} sourcetype={SOURCETYPE} earliest=-24h
| Comment: | rare limit=20 {FIELD_NAME}

| Comment: --- Alternative: Field value correlation ---

| Comment: index={INDEX} sourcetype={SOURCETYPE} earliest=-24h
| Comment: | stats count by {FIELD1}, {FIELD2}
| Comment: | sort - count
```
